 <br>
If you are looking to buy some new tools, whether you are a home repair guru, a DIY enthusiast, a tool lover, or a professional in need of high quality and diverse tool arsenal, one of the popular brands you might be looking into is Makita.

 <br>
 <br>
 <br>
Of course, you want the best products that your money can buy, and this means knowing what the brand has to offer. With that in mind, today we review Makita, specifically in terms of quality and product selection.

Is this a good tool brand?

 <br>
 <br>
Long Story Short…
Makita
A Japanese brand with more than a hundred-year history and an excellent selection of power tools. Recommended for serious amateurs and even professionals.
Shop Makita on Amazon

Before we get into a full-blown review of the brand, it is worth knowing what its history is like. Makita is a Japanese manufacturer of power tools and related products. It was founded in Aichi Prefecture by Mosabura Makita who first started the company under the Makita Electric Works Company name.
 <br>
 <br>

The company first started by making and selling lighting equipment, motors, and transformers. However, the Japanese tool market seemed to be void of any big-time tool manufacturers at the time, and by 1960, Makita had realized the potential of manufacturing and selling power tools.

What is important to note is that Makita is a great brand to consider if you are looking for power tools, power tool accessories, and outdoor power equipment, as these are the product categories that it mainly focuses on.
        
        
